{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    if input_grid.shape[0] > input_grid.shape[1]:\n        output_grid, direction = pan_green_pixels(output_grid)\n        output_grid = fill_teal_rectangles(output_grid, direction)\n    else:\n        output_grid, direction = pan_green_pixels_lr(output_grid)\n        output_grid = fill_teal_rectangles(output_grid, direction)\n    return output_grid\ndef pan_green_pixels_lr(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and pans the green pixels left or right many pixels until they are adjacent to the red pixels in the output_grid.\n    It returns the output grid and the direction of the pan (1 for left and -1 for right).\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the output grid and the direction of the pan (1 for left and -1 for right)\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    direction = 1\n    green_pixels = np.where(output_grid == green)\n    red_pixels = np.where(output_grid == red)\n    if green_pixels[1][0] > red_pixels[1][0]:\n        direction = -1\n    while green_pixels[1][0] != red_pixels[1][0]:\n        output_grid = np.roll(output_grid, direction, axis=1)\n        green_pixels = np.where(output_grid == green)\n    return (output_grid, direction)\ndef pan_green_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[np.ndarray, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and pans the green pixels up or down many pixels until they are adjacent to the red pixels in the output_grid.\n    It returns the output grid and the direction of the pan (1 for up and -1 for down).\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the output grid and the direction of the pan (1 for up and -1 for down)\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = input_grid.copy